items.name: Art Universe
items.description:
Welcome to Art Universe

Special thanks for the opportunity to use LORA from Clumsy_Trainer.

This model was created by mixing several different models with each other, as well as adding about 10 LORA. This is an interesting model for creating images in the style of comics or cartoons.

The CFG scale must be at most 6 and the sampling steps must be at least 28. I recommend using hires and upscaler. I usually use Clip Skip 1.

"Bad-hands-5" and "EasyNegative" are great for embedding negativity.

I use ADetailer to restore faces.

This branch of models is a continuation of my work on UniverseStable models. These were the first models in which I did not adhere to a single style, there are also photorealistic models, magazine photography, artistic retouching, analog photography, a fantasy model, as well as two comic and animation models. I will be glad if you show interest in this work.

Sweet potato balls are a popular Taiwanese snack made from sweet potato, flour, and sugar. They are typically deep-fried and then coated in a sweet and savory sauce. Sweet potato balls are a delicious and versatile snack that can be enjoyed by people of all ages. They can be eaten as a snack, dessert, or even as a main course.

Sweet potato balls are made by first boiling sweet potatoes until they are soft. The sweet potatoes are then mashed and mixed with flour and sugar. The dough is then rolled into small balls and deep-fried until golden brown. The fried sweet potato balls are then coated in a sweet and savory sauce, which is typically made from soy sauce, sugar, sesame oil, and chili peppers.

Sweet potato balls are a delicious and nutritious snack that is perfect for a quick bite on the go. They are also a great source of carbohydrates and fiber, which can help to keep you feeling full and satisfied. If you are looking for a delicious and healthy snack, sweet potato balls are a great option

items.name: Sōichirō Yamamoto Style [Takagi-san, Kunoichi Tsubaki and more]
items.description:
Makes images in style similar to Sōichirō Yamamoto famous for his series "Teasing Master Takagi-san" and "In the Heart of Kunoichi Tsubaki" to name a few.
This is a LyCORIS version of the previously released LoRA, updated with more recent images and retagged.

How to use
Just prompt away. Things this LyCORIS are good at is, naturally, smugs and foreheads.
Different samplers gives different looks, Euler A gives a more clean look while Karras M tends to draw more on a drawn style - experiment to see what you like best. For models with realism mixed in like AOM2 I recommend putting "3D" and/or "realism" in negatives.
Using these tips this LyCORIS is quite versatile in what in can output.

Misc
Trained on NAI at 512 res. Dataset of 160 images.
All images are untouched txt2img upscaled, no inpainting or helper embeddings used for quality transparence, e.g. - things should look even better if you do.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LoRA is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the source material. Go support the artist if you want the good stuff.

items.name: David Lynch's Ronnie Rocket
items.description:
David Lynch's surreal project about a detective with a twisted sense of reality and his adventures in a bizarre world was never completed.

Plot and Concept: "Ronnie Rocket" is described as a surreal and darkly fantastical story set in a dystopian city. The titular character, Ronnie Rocket, is a three-foot-tall man with a bright red crew cut and physical deformities. He possesses a unique ability to generate electricity. The narrative is said to involve Ronnie's journey through a twisted urban landscape, exploring themes of identity, duality, and the human experience.

Influences: Lynch's work often draws from his fascination with dreams, subconscious imagery, and the darker aspects of human nature. "Ronnie Rocket" was expected to delve into these themes, much like Lynch's other works.

Reasons for Non-Completion: Despite its intriguing premise and Lynch's dedication to the project, "Ronnie Rocket" faced numerous challenges that prevented its completion. Funding issues, creative differences, and other obstacles reportedly contributed to the film's abandonment. Lynch himself has rarely discussed the project in detail, contributing to its enigmatic status.

Legacy and Impact: While "Ronnie Rocket" was never completed, its existence continues to capture the imagination of Lynch's fans and film enthusiasts. The project's mysterious nature has led to speculation about what the finished film might have been like, and it has become a symbol of Lynch's unique and unconventional approach to filmmaking.

It's important to note that much of the information available about "Ronnie Rocket" is based on interviews, anecdotes, and fragments of details shared by Lynch and those involved in the film industry. As a result, the specifics of the film's plot and development remain shrouded in mystery. Despite its status as an unfinished project, "Ronnie Rocket" remains an intriguing part of David Lynch's filmography and a subject of fascination for those interested in his work.

items.name: SDXL Detail Enhanced/Simplified - 细节增强/简化
items.description:
这是一个可以通过改变权重来调节画面整体细节的LoRA，其对背景的作用尤为明显。该LoRA适用于各类2D，2.5D和3D模型。

你也可以通过将其以特定权重融合到大模型中，从而获得细节更丰富、背景更充实，或，画风更简化、线条更简洁的风格的模型。

This LoRA allows you to adjust the overall level of detail by modifying its weights, with a particularly noticeable impact on the background. This LoRA is versatile, suitable for various 2D, 2.5D, and 3D SDXL models.

You can also merge it with specific weights into a base model to achieve different styles, such as more intricate backgrounds and richer details, or simplified and cleaner lines.

使用建议 Usage Guideline

  1. 在负值权重下，背景的近景会显著变清晰，远处细节如楼房等立面的复杂度会增加，人物头发及衣服线条细节增加。在正值权重下，背景变得更模糊，人物的线条细节也会得到简化。需注意，对于一些2D模型，由于线条和色块的复杂度也被用于区分不同的风格，所以当你在使用这个LoRA改变细节时，也会对2D画风有一定影响。

    When using negative weights, the foreground of the background becomes significantly clearer, and distant elements like building facades gain complexity. Moreover, finer details in characters' hair and clothing will be enhanced. Conversely, positive weights lead to a more blurred background and simplified lines in characters. Note that when applying this LoRA to some 2D models, as lines and color blocks are also used to differentiate styles, altering the details with LoRA might impact the 2D style to some extent.

  2. 权重取值建议：建议先从-1到1进行尝试，再根据效果进行调整。根据我对于目前的SDXL模型的测试经验，如果你使用拟合程度较高（过拟合）的base模型，那么建议保持此LoRA权重在-1到1之间。而对于一些拟合程度良好，泛化性优异的模型，则可以在权重-2到2之间使用此LoRA.

    Suggested weight values: It is recommended to start with weights ranging from -1 to 1 and then adjust according to the desired effects. Based on my testing experience with the current SDXL models, if you are using a base model with a high degree of fitting (overfitting), it is advisable to keep the LoRA weights within the range of -1 to 1. For models with excellent generalization and fitting, you may experiment with LoRA weights between -2 and 2.

#Update 1.8.22

  • Automatically save output at drive ( Export/ComfyUI )

  • Basic usage: Run with Version ComfyUI, select Prune if you want to download less controlnet, choose checkpoint at the library if you want to download more, Model SDVN3 is installed by default, click on the cloudflare link at the beginning of part 2 to use.

🔔 Version : Kohya (Kohya_ss GUI Trainer)

  • Works with Checkpoint library

  • The features work normally, the caption running part may appear error, the lora SDXL training part requires the use of GPU A100

🔔 Version : SDXL

  • Optimized for maximum performance to run SDXL with colab free

  • Only works with checkpoint library

  • Automatically load specific settings that are best optimized for SDXL

  • Auto Load SDXL 1.0

  • If you want to use more checkpoints: Download more to the drive or paste the link / select in the library section

  • Pre-installed compatible extensions: Dynamic prompt / After Detailer / Style by SDXL

🔔 Versions A-1.3 and A-1.41 :

  • Works with all options

🔔 A1111-Update versions:

  • This is the default selected version

  • Can run SDXL and SD 1.5 (Requires colab prom to run SDXL), when you want to run SDXL with A-update, it is recommended to check SDXLMode at the beginning of part 2 to run SDXL's own settings. If SDXLMode is not selected, be sure to change Vae to auto when running SDXL.

  • When choosing this version: Commonly used Lycos like Lora, Lora block weights use different syntax, refer to

🔔 Checkpoint library:

  • Update new library list : More, newer

  • Add option : SaveFromMyDrive - Helps to download the selected checkpoint directly or pasted the download link in the custom link to the model folder on Drive instead of temporarily saving it on colab

🔔 QRControlnet :

  • Support 4 types of controlnet serving as QR

🔔 Extensions:

💡 How to install the Extension individually:

  • At the A1111 Ui interface, go to the Wildcard section => Press Reset => Select the MyExtensionList card => Enter the github extension link line by line in the right text box, press Save.

  • Unused extensions, go to Extensions, uncheck => Save

  • From the next run, the Extensions will be installed completely as you like

💡 How to set token to run Ngrok server only once:

  • Get Ngrok token: here

  • At the A1111 Ui interface, go to the Wildcard section => Press Reset => Select the Ngroktoken card => Paste the ngrok token link in the right text box, press Save

  • From the next Ui run, there will always be an Ngrok server appearing before the Gradio sever, running the Ngrok server will be stable and less error prone.

💡How to share drive data:

  • After running WebUi for the first time with the main account, an SD-Data folder will be created on the main account's Drive

  • At the main account Drive, Right-click the SD-Data folder, select share => Enter sub accounts and authorize read and write

  • At Drive sub-account, go to Shared => Right-click on SD-Data folder, select add shortcut => Create shortcut to Drive, make sure SD-Data folder is unique on secondary account.

  • From next time, the secondary account using Ui web will always use the same data library as the main account

items.name: Zdzislaw Beksinski SDXL 1.0 art style lora
items.description:
If you like what I do please consider supporting me on Patreon and contributing your ideas to my future projects!

Zdzislaw Beksinski art style lora for SDXL 1.0. Zdzislaw Beksinski is a dystopian surrealist artist and now you can generate art similar to his style within your own Stable Diffusion workflow. This model was trained on 1024 x 1024 resolution and is able to produce higher details than if you were to simply put his name into your prompt.

I use this at a weight of around 1 but you may have to go a little lower sometimes depending on the prompt. I used clip skip 1 for all of the images you see uploaded to this page. CFG 7 seems to be the ideal setting for this art style but feel free to experiment.

In addition to the main trigger b3ks1n which you can use on its own you can also use these additional custom tags to provide more variation. When using these you may have to adjust LoRa weight periodically. The best way to use them would be to put them in a wildcard and add one or two to your prompt or to play around with each one individually and see which ones you like best. They are meant to provide variety on top of the main trigger tag.

4pp4r1

by4r

h3lm3

str1c

str1n

gh05

m0n0

3cl1s

d151tgr

b1r1e

j4l0p

cr4d31

c4rre

h4nu0n

h41wy

3bm4rc

l4no3

r14nb

Since the dataset was acquired from various sources across the web I do not have all of the names of each painting those trigger words were trained on. They are obfuscated in 1337 speak so that the SDXL AI does not misinterpret them. Until dreambooth gets implemented into kohya custom captioning wont work the way it did in SD1.5 so this is the best I can do for now.

Have fun playing around with this remarkable tech and if you like it be sure to review and upload all of your amazing works of art!

items.name: Whitebox Style - Environment - Level Design Concept Art - Game Dev Tool
items.description:
It's dangerous to go alone! Take this LoRA!

Use this LoRA to create grayscale environment concept art to help coming up with ideas for level layouts and scenes.

The model is trained on generated images only.

Usage

Use the trigger word: "WhiteboxStyle" along with the LoRA to use it.

Recommended weight: 0.4-1.0

Recommended sampling method: Euler a

Tips & Tricks

If you're getting too much color, try adding "monochrome" to your prompt

Not enough colors? Add some accents or colors by writing the name of the color at the start of the prompt.

Higher weights tend to give you more sharpness and more abstract shapes.

Useful keywords for the prompt:

  • indoor can be used to set the location to be indoors.

  • platform / bridge / path lets you add more places for characters to walk.

  • cubes / blocky / box adds cubes and blocky shapes to your levels, can be good for platforms.

  • lowpoly / low-poly can add a bit of a lowpoly effect to your level, but it's not part of the training data.

Recommended models

GAME DEV TOOLS 03 / TOPO

Locations to explore

  • rooftops

  • dilapidated

  • dungeon

  • temple

  • moonbase

  • mansion

  • city

  • library

  • warehouse

  • factory

  • nuclear facility

  • lab

  • post-apocalypse

Prompt keywords to add detail

  • overgrown

  • wires

  • wireframe

items.name: George A. Romero's Twilight of the Dead
items.description:
"Twilight of the Dead" was a planned film project by legendary filmmaker George A. Romero, who is best known for revolutionizing the zombie genre with his classic film "Night of the Living Dead" (1968) and its subsequent sequels. "Twilight of the Dead" was intended to be another installment in Romero's zombie film series, following his earlier works like "Dawn of the Dead" (1978) and "Day of the Dead" (1985).

Here's what is known about the project:

  1. Concept and Development: George A. Romero had been discussing and developing "Twilight of the Dead" for several years. The film was envisioned as a direct continuation of the narrative established in his previous zombie films, exploring the ongoing struggle of human survivors in a world overrun by the undead.

  2. Script and Story: While details about the specific plot of "Twilight of the Dead" are limited, it was expected to delve deeper into the post-apocalyptic world inhabited by both humans and zombies. Romero's films often included social commentary, and "Twilight of the Dead" was likely to address relevant themes in a similar vein.

  3. Production Challenges: Despite Romero's reputation and the enduring popularity of his earlier zombie films, "Twilight of the Dead" faced challenges in securing funding and production support. The film industry landscape had changed significantly since Romero's earlier successes, and financing original projects, especially in the horror genre, could be difficult.

  4. Romero's Passing: Tragically, George A. Romero passed away on July 16, 2017, before he was able to fully realize "Twilight of the Dead." His death marked the end of an era for the zombie genre and left the future of the project uncertain.

  5. Legacy and Influence: George A. Romero's contributions to the zombie genre are immeasurable, and his influence can be seen in countless films, television shows, and other media. While "Twilight of the Dead" was never completed, Romero's earlier works continue to inspire filmmakers and storytellers.

  6. Potential Future Projects: Following Romero's death, there have been discussions about potentially continuing his legacy through projects related to the zombie genre. For example, his wife, Suzanne Desrocher-Romero, expressed interest in pursuing projects that would honor his legacy, potentially including unfinished works like "Twilight of the Dead."

It's important to note that the information available about "Twilight of the Dead" is limited, and specific details about the plot, characters, and production status are not widely known. The project's development challenges and Romero's untimely passing ultimately prevented the film from being realized.

As you can see from the sample images it's possible to get decent 3D outputs as well as 2D plus anything ranging from oh-thats-cute to please-god-make-her-eat-my-head-first-so-I-don't-have-to-suffer. I didn't upload any samples of the latter because it was frankly a bit hard finding something not too nightmarish to share.
For further prompt tips see the uploaded zip of training tags.


Misc
Dataset of 46 images trained at 512 on NAI.
All images are untouched txt2img upscaled, no inpainting or helper embeddings used for quality transparence, e.g. - things should look even better if you do.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LoRA is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the source material. Go support the artist if you want the good stuff.
